\ls1\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 A large team that needed to develop features in parallel\
\ls1\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Pressure to deliver new business capabilities quickly\
\ls1\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Limited ability to refactor safely because the system had little technical safety net\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec3 The immediate problem was not simply that the application was old. The larger issue was that the team lacked the engineering foundation needed to make controlled changes at scale.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 \strokec3 My Role\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 \strokec3 As architect, I was responsible for defining the modernization strategy, establishing development practices, guiding architectural changes, and helping the team extend the system safely.\
My responsibilities included:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
